  "decision_conditions": [
    "CONDITION: The development shall be designed in accordance with the principles of Inclusive Design. To achieve this the development shall incorporate/install:\r\na) Ground Floor Drying Room Door Width The width of door to the drying room should be either 800 or 825 in accordance with Part M Vol 2 Table 2.\r\nb) Drying Room Hanging Facilities The room must incorporate reachable hanging facilities to enable wheelchair users.\r\nc) First Floor Shower Room Doors These should open outwards in accordance with Part\r\nM vol 2 5.4 e. These doors need to be openable from the outside in case someone needed assistance or appeared to trapped inside. It is acknowledged that these doors will partly obstruct the corridor - can the agent address this through design?\r\nd) Shelter Stairs to Shower Rooms from Elements A shelter for the stairs and approach for the first floor shower facility would be preferable, to ensure the facility is appealing to use, thus promotes cycling.\r\n\r\nThe development shall be carried out strictly in accordance with the details so approved, shall be maintained as such thereafter and no change there from shall take place without the prior written consent of the Local Planning Authority\r\n\r\nREASON: In order to facilitate and promote inclusive and sustainable communities."
